  "active_lock_reason": null,
  "body": "I think the semantics of `@nonreentrant(<key-name>)` are a little difficult to describe to the average user, and that allowing a default value (perhaps `lock`) under the hood would reduce confusion to those trying to use this feature. You could then specify it without the parents syntax as just `@nonreentrant` which would make it easier to use, and safer for those untrained in how to use the more advanced functionality of this feature.",
